{{Infobox book | name = Still Life | image = Still Life (novel).jpg | author = [[Louise Penny]] | genre = [[Mystery fiction]] | published = 2005 | publisher = [[St. Martin's Paperbacks]] | isbn = 978-0-312-94855-9 | alt = Still Life | pages = 293 | website = {{URL|http://www.louisepenny.com/books.htm|Still Life}} | awards = [[Anthony Award|Anthony Award for Best First Novel]] (2007) }}
'''Still Life''' is a novel written by [[Louise Penny]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=R_HjCQAAQBAJ&source=gbs_navlinks_s|title=Still Life: 1|last=Penny|first=Louise|date=2015-07-07|publisher=Little, Brown Book Group|isbn=9780751563627|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.louisepenny.com/books.htm|title=Louise Penny Author - Official site|website=www.louisepenny.com|access-date=2017-03-24}}</ref> and published by [[St. Martin's Paperbacks]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/still-life-louise-penny/1100355026|title=Still Life (Chief Inspector Gamache Series #1)|last=Noble|first=Barnes &|website=Barnes & Noble|language=en|access-date=2017-03-24}}</ref> (an imprint of [[Macmillan Publishers]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://us.macmillan.com/stilllife/louisepenny/9780312541538/|title=Still Life {{!}} Louise Penny {{!}} Macmillan|work=US Macmillan|access-date=2017-03-24|language=en-US}}</ref> owned by [[Holtzbrinck Publishing Group]]) on 1 January 2005, which later went on to win the [[Anthony Award]] for Best First Novel in 2007.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/2000s/|title=Winners and Nominees 2000s|date=2015-09-22|work=Bouchercon|access-date=2017-03-24|language=en}}</ref>
==Plot Intro== A body is found in the woods near a small town called Three Pines. Inspector Gamache and his homicide team are sent to investigate. {{main|Chief Inspector Armand Gamache}} == References == <references />
